Docs.summary: A NumericShaper.Range represents a Unicode range of a script having its own decimal digits.

remarks.para: A NumericShaper.Range represents a Unicode range of a script having its own decimal digits. For example, the NumericShaper.Range#THAI range has the Thai digits, THAI DIGIT ZERO (U+0E50) to THAI DIGIT NINE (U+0E59).

The Range enum replaces the traditional bit mask-based values (e.g., NumericShaper#ARABIC), and supports more Unicode ranges than the bit mask-based ones. For example, the following code using the bit mask: <blockquote>
can be written using this enum as:
Added in 1.7.
